The sculpture was intended to represent the relationship between the French and American republics through a banal classic figure - the female image of Liberty.
Lazarus changed her meaning: in her poem, the female figure is no longer abstract, she has a voice.
And she got a completely different name: Mother of the Exile.
The combination of poetry and image was a brilliant feminist move and a devastating attack on American nativism.
And how Lazarus changed the meaning of the statue, the right though change it back.
The loud-mouthed Rush Limbaugh, a sort of John the Baptist who announced Trump's arrival, argued in 2010 that Freedom is not inviting anyone, but rather an early neoconservative, carrying America's flame to a world in darkness: "Freedom is moving forward.
