Colin claims that this is not the case, but accuses Paul of incompetent management of some facilities.
In the deposition Colin gave at the start of the trial, he says he hopes to resolve the dispute.
"My Italian roots make me consider my family a top priority", he wrote.
The legal costs are skyrocketing, with hundreds of pages of depositions, emails and reports from companies like Deloitte, Pitcher Partners and Charter Keck Cramer, and both sides have attracted the best lawyers, including the Queen's Counsel Alan Myers, and the best dressers.
Mrs. De Lutyens and her late husband Luigi were Italian immigrants; they ran dairy bars and food stores from the late 1950s, and in the early 1970s bought a store in Brunswick.
