In Ukraine , they suggested sending Russians to prison for illegally crossing the border
The Ukrainian parliament has approved a bill that would impose criminal penalties on Russians for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, a document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament implies a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens who try to illegally enter the country.
It is noted that for repeated offenses or acts committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the offender was caught at the border with a weapon, the term of imprisonment for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians trying to get into Russia outside the established checkpoints.
