Russia will have two new territories of rapid social and economic development - "Abaz" and "Novotroytsk".
The relevant decisions of the Russian Government will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In a city with 15 thousand inhabitants, there will be a special legal regime for entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments by residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, as well as create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of economic activities, in which the special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity will operate in the "Abaz" TOR, includes, for example, plant breeding, animal husbandry, production of food products, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
The Republic's Government has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise of the "Abaka mine" LLC.
In January 2017, the regional authorities reported that Khakassia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroytsk, a territory of rapid social and economic development will also be created.
This will allow diversification of the economy of the monogoround, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of Ural Steel JSC, as well as create more than 2,3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 million rubles.
The list of economic activities that will be subject to a special legal regime for entrepreneurs in the new TOR includes, in particular, freshwater fishing, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroytsk became the first of the monogorooms of the Orenburg region to receive the status of a tourist destination.
Recall that the area of rapid development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
The following benefits are available to residents of the TOR: a profit tax of no more than 5% for the first five years and no less than 10% for the next five years, social contributions of 7,6% for 10 years, use of the free customs zone regime, a preferential regime for connecting to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates on rent.
